  "slug": "fluffy-pancakes",
  "title": "Fluffy Pancakes",
  "subtitle": "Thick, soft American-style pancakes with a fluffy interior",
  "excerpt": "A straightforward American pancake batter of flour, baking powder, egg, milk, and butter, cooked on a buttered pan until the edges set and bubbles break across the surface. Thick, soft inside, and lightly golden. Makes enough for four, served stacked.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal collection, an American-style pancake recipe she has made many times in her own kitchen.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thick American-style pancakes, soft and fluffy inside with a lightly golden crust. The baking powder gives them their lift; too much stirring knocks it out. Mix until the dry flour just disappears, then leave the batter to rest for two minutes before cooking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A medium-low heat gives the pancakes time to puff and cook through before the base colours too fast. When bubbles break across the surface and the edges look set, the pancake is ready to flip.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Plain flour",
              "unit": "cup",
              "amount": 1.5,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f2xb0000rkv47vd545ba",
              "ingredientSlug": "plain-flour"
            },
            {
              "name": "Baking powder",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 4,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f91k00asrkv4txgq60ov",
              "ingredientSlug": "baking-powder"
            },
            {
              "name": "Fine sea salt",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7kz0086rkv4lsr8ds3o",
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
            },
            {
              "name": "Caster sugar",
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "amount": 3,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": true,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fau900dvrkv4ce3mot41",
              "ingredientSlug": "caster-sugar"
            },
            {
              "name": "Eggs",
              "unit": "each",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3wj001prkv40f7svjvg",
              "ingredientSlug": "eggs"
            },
            {
              "name": "Whole milk",
              "unit": "cup",
              "amount": 1.25,
              "prepNote": "or almond milk",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3be000nrkv4co43fp6z",
              "ingredientSlug": "whole-milk"
            },
            {
              "name": "Salted butter",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "or vegan butter",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3h0000xrkv4pb5h36z0",
              "ingredientSlug": "salted-butter"
            },
            {
              "name": "Vanilla extract",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f97x00b3rkv4kdhng3ak",
              "ingredientSlug": "vanilla-extract"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a large bowl add the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Use a whisk or wooden spoon to combine the ingredients together well. Set to the side.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a smaller bowl crack in the egg. Pour in the milk and vanilla extract.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Melt the butter in the microwave or in a small saucepan over low heat and add to the bowl.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Use a fork or whisk to mix the ingredients together until well combined.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Make a well in the dry ingredients and pour in the wet.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Fold the batter together with a wooden spoon until there is no longer any dry flour. There will be a few small lumps in the batter, this is perfectly okay. Make sure to not over mix the batter as this will cause your pancakes to be rubbery and tough.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat a heavy based frypan like a cast iron skillet over medium low heat. When the pan is hot add a knob of butter and wait until it melts.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Measure out ⅓ cup of the pancake batter and pour it into the pan. Let it spread on its own.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cook the pancake for 2-3 minutes or until the edges are set and bubbles are popping in the middle.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Use a spatula to flip the pancake over and cook for a further 2-3 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Repeat with the remaining batter.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve the pancakes stacked, topped with butter and maple syrup.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Lower the heat to medium-low and wait for bubbles to break across the surface before flipping. The first side takes 2 to 3 minutes; a raw centre means the pan is too hot.",
              "cause": "Heat too high; flipped too soon.",
              "symptom": "Pancakes brown outside but raw inside"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stir only until the dry flour disappears. Lumps are fine. Over-mixed batter develops gluten and produces flat, tough pancakes.",
              "cause": "Batter over-mixed.",
              "symptom": "Pancakes flat and tough"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check the baking powder is fresh. It loses lift after six months. Replace and test again.",
              "cause": "Baking powder stale or too little used.",
              "symptom": "Pancakes don't puff"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Weigh the flour. Cup measures vary by up to 20 percent depending on how you scoop. Too much flour produces a dry, heavy result.",
              "cause": "Too much flour, or batter too stiff.",
              "symptom": "Pancakes dense and heavy"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Citrus version: replace the vanilla with the zest of an orange or lemon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dairy-free: swap the whole milk for oat or almond milk, and use a plant-based butter.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "American-style pancakes are thicker and softer than the thin crepes common in Britain and France. They are a Sunday breakfast dish, often served stacked with maple syrup and a knob of butter melting between the layers. The baking powder batter is the defining feature; the high lift makes them the centrepiece of the plate rather than a wrapper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
